2. Categories of Personal Information Collected

InMarket collects, and has collected in the past 12 months, the following categories of personal information:

(a) personal identifiers (for example, your name (either first, last or both), email address, postal address, zip code, phone number, mobile advertising identifier, IP address, and cookie ID);
(b) protected information under the California Customer Records statute (Cal. Civ. Code § 1798.80(e)), (for example, your first and last name, or financial information);
(c) protected class characteristics (for example, gender);
(d) commercial information (for example, records of purchases made, records of purchases considered, consuming histories and tendencies, purchase transaction receipts, shopping lists). When you connect your bank account to an InMarket Application, we will collect your purchase transaction details including vendor category, date, amount, merchant name, merchant description and personal finance category, merchant name. When you connect your retail accounts (such as an online store user account or retail store loyalty account) to your Unflation application, we will receive full access to the accounts you link. InMarket will not use this access to make purchases or change items in your shopping cart. We will collect item-level purchase data each day, including the item names and details, date, quantity, price and transaction total using your account info and other store data;
(e) internet activity information (for example, information regarding your interactions with a website, mobile application or advertisement, device operating system, browser type‚ referring website, the pages viewed on the website or application, and the application name and version, social profile data);
(f) precise geolocation, which is a category of “Sensitive Personal Information” under the California Consumer Privacy Act of 2018, as modified by the Consumer Privacy Rights Act of 2020 (CCPA as defined below), and is a category of “Sensitive Data” under the Virginia Consumer Data Protection Act (VCDPA as defined below);
(g) inferences drawn from personal information to create a consumer profile (for example, profiles regarding consumer preferences, behavior, or interests); and
(h) Certain information we collect, or inferences we may make, may reveal racial or ethnic origin, religious or philosophical beliefs, or sexual orientation, which may be “Sensitive Data” under the VCDPA and “Sensitive Personal Information” under the CCPA.

6. Sale of Personal Information

According to the definitions and terms included in the California Consumer Privacy Act of 2018 and other California state privacy laws and regulations (we collectively call these laws the “CCPA”), in the past 12 months InMarket has sold its Third Party Partners some consumer personal information that falls within these categories:

(a) personal identifiers;
(b) protected personal information under the California Customer Records statute (Cal. Civ. Code § 1798.80(e));
(c) protected class characteristics;
(d) commercial information;
(e) internet activity information;
(f) geolocation data/precise geolocation information; and
(g) inferences drawn from personal information to create a consumer profile.

7. Disclosure of Personal Information

According to the definitions and terms included in the CCPA, in the past 12 months, InMarket has disclosed for business purposes some consumer personal information that falls within these categories:

(a) personal identifiers, which we disclosed to some customers, customers’ vendors, Third Party Partners, and our vendors and service providers for the purpose of auditing compliance with advertising specifications and agreements; detecting security issues; logging and debugging errors; performing services for InMarket, including storing records, transaction fulfillment, processing payments, advertising and marketing services, analytics services, and related services; internal research for technological development; and activities to improve and enhance InMarket’s services;
(b) protected personal information under the California Customer Records statute (Cal. Civ. Code § 1798.80(e)), which we disclosed to some customers, customers’ vendors, Third Party Partners, and our vendors and service providers for the purpose of auditing compliance with advertising specifications and agreements; detecting security issues; logging and debugging errors; performing services for InMarket, including storing records, transaction fulfillment, processing payments, advertising and marketing services, analytics services, and related services; internal research for technological development; and activities to improve and enhance InMarket’s services; 
(c) protected class characteristics, which we disclosed to some customers, customers’ vendors, Third Party Partners, and our vendors and service providers for the purpose of performing services for InMarket, including storing records, transaction fulfillment, processing payments, advertising and marketing services, analytics services, and related services;
(d) commercial information, which we disclosed to some customers, customers’ vendors, Third Party Partners, and our vendors and service providers for the purpose of performing services for InMarket, including storing records, transaction fulfillment, processing payments, advertising and marketing services, analytics services, and related services; internal research for technological development; and activities to improve and enhance InMarket’s services; 
(e) internet activity information, which we disclosed to some customers, customers’ vendors, Third Party Partners, and our vendors and service providers for the purpose of auditing compliance with advertising specifications and agreements; detecting security issues; logging and debugging errors; performing services for InMarket, including storing records, transaction fulfillment, processing payments, advertising and marketing services, analytics services, and related services; internal research for technological development; and activities to improve and enhance InMarket’s services; 
(f) precise geolocation information, which we disclosed to some customers, customers’ vendors, Third Party Partners, and our vendors and service providers for the purpose of auditing compliance with advertising specifications and agreements; detecting security issues; logging and debugging errors; performing services for InMarket, including storing records, transaction fulfillment, processing payments, advertising and marketing services, analytics services, and related services; internal research for technological development; activities to improve and enhance InMarket’s services; and 
(g) inferences drawn from personal information to create a consumer profile, which we disclosed to some customers, customers’ vendors, Third Party Partners, and our vendors and service providers for the purpose of auditing compliance with advertising specifications and agreements; performing services for InMarket, including storing records, transaction fulfillment, processing payments, advertising and marketing services, analytics services, and related services; internal research for technological development; activities to improve and enhance InMarket’s services.

